["The issues mentioned are related to the transition from Java EE to Jakarta EE. In the process of migrating Java EE 8 to Jakarta EE 8, the namespace of the imported classes has changed from `javax.*` to `jakarta.*`. \n\nQuarkus uses Jakarta EE 8, so we need to change the import statements in the Java class to use the `jakarta.*` namespace.\n\nThe annotations `@RequestScoped`, `@Inject`, `@Path`, `@Consumes`, `@Produces`, `@GET`, and `@PathParam` used in the Java class are part of Jakarta EE 8 APIs and their classes are in the `jakarta.*` namespace.\n\nAfter modifying the import statements, there's no need to change the pom.xml file, because Quarkus already includes the Jakarta EE API in its dependencies.\n\nSo, the changes required are:\n\n1. Replace `javax.enterprise.context.RequestScoped` with `jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped`.\n2. Replace `javax.inject.Inject` with `jakarta.inject.Inject`.\n3. Replace `javax.ws.rs.Consumes` with `jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes`.\n4. Replace `javax.ws.rs.GET` with `jakarta.ws.rs.GET`.\n5. Replace `javax.ws.rs.Path` with `jakarta.ws.rs.Path`.\n6. Replace `javax.ws.rs.PathParam` with `jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam`.\n7. Replace `javax.ws.rs.Produces` with `jakarta.ws.rs.Produces`.\n8. Replace `javax.ws.rs.core.MediaType` with `jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType`."]